      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SMOOTH BUCKAROO (9) is racing well having only once missed the placings in his last six starts and that came against stronger company in a Nutrien heat. Has been racing well from this row, scoring from this barrier two runs back before racing wide without cover but fighting well to be beaten less than 2m last week. Draws for a nice trail so can atone. COWBOY CULTURE (10) has been a model of consistency of late and deserved his success here last start, working from a wide barrier before digging deep. Beat SMOOTH BUCKAROO home there and could overcome the back row draw to do it again. WIT WICKEE (7) ended last prep with a win at Parkes seven months ago. Draws wide but was readied with two nice trials so is capable of a forward showing while fresh. MONTRELL (4) did some work when finishing fourth first-up here last time out. Fitter and is lightly raced so has upside.",
